DENGUE/DHF - VIETNAM (02)
*************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Dengue/DHF - Vietnam 980429201122
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 1998 07:16:49 -0700
From: Dr. Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on dengue in Vietnam were extracted from the
GIDEON software program:
Cases occur year round in the South, and during the rainy season elsewhere.
Disease among adults is more common in the North.
The first cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) were reported in 1958, in
the Hanoi area.
Approximately 50 fatal cases of DHF were reported from Cai-Be (Dinh Tuong
Province) in 1960.
An outbreak of several hundred cases, and over 100 deaths, was reported in
1963.
An outbreak in the North during 1969 infected 25,900 in Hanoi, and 6,956
in Haiphong.
242 cases (38 fatal) of DHF were reported in 1970 (of which 196
cases and 36 deaths were reported from Kien-Giang Province)
93 (22 fatal) in 1971 (63, 15 fatal from Kien-Giang)
1,670 (219 fatal) in 1972
14,320 (986 fatal) in 1973
4,621 (438 fatal) in 1974.
30,799 cases of DHF (16,328 in Ho Chi Minh City/ 1,183 in Hanoi) were
reported in 1975
25,722 (3,886/1,274) in 1976
40,544 (6,035/6,139) in 1977
43,684 (14,777/3,656) in 1978
63,976 (14,684/5,234) in 1979
95,146 (5,340/3,706) in 1980
35,323 (4,129/2,402) in 1981 - 408 fatal;
39,806 (6,391/1,112) in 1982 - 353 fatal;
157,709 (26,398/4,776) in 1983 - 1,811 fatal.
30,496 cases of DHF (368 fatal) were reported in 1984
45,107 (399) in 1985
46,266 (511) in 1986
354,517 (1,566) in 1987
85,160 (826) in 1988
40,205 (289) in 1989
54,767 (246) in 1990
111,817 cases of DHF (445 fatal) were reported in 1991
51,311 (271) in 1992
53,674 (157) in 1993
44,944 in 1994
80,447 in 1995
86,621 (124) in 1996.
16.6% of the latter were reported from Tien Giang, 14.2% from the Mekong
Delta, 14.1%
from Minh Hai, 11.4% from Kien Gikang, 8.7% from Ho Chi Minh City and 7.3%
from Dong Nai.
